<p>Outstanding value picks include <strong>Charles Krug Family Reserve Cabernet ($35-40)</strong> and <strong>Frank Family Vineyard Cabernet ($45-50)</strong>, both delivering complexity rivaling $75+ bottles. When reading labels, prioritize <strong>"Estate Grown"</strong> designations indicating single-property fruit, <strong>specific AVA appellations</strong> like Oakville or Rutherford over generic "Napa Valley," and <strong>alcohol levels between 14.5-15.5%</strong>, suggesting balanced ripeness.</p>

