<p><strong>2018 and 2019 vintages</strong> are drinking beautifully now, offering immediate gratification with fully integrated tannins. <strong>2020 and 2021</strong> represent excellent cellaring candidates, requiring 3-5 years to reach optimal drinking windows. The challenging <strong>2017 vintage</strong> produced concentrated wines at reduced quantities, making them premium investments.</p>

<h3>Smart Shopping and Storage</h3>
<p>Purchase from <strong>established wine shops</strong> offering proper storage and knowledgeable staff, or trusted online retailers like Wine.com and K&L Wine Merchants. <strong>Avoid auction houses</strong> unless seeking mature vintages, as provenance can be questionable.</p>

<p>Store purchases in a <strong>55-65°F environment</strong> with consistent humidity. Wines under $50 typically benefit from 1-2 years additional cellaring, while premium bottles ($75+) reward patience with 5-10 years aging. Invest in proper wine storage for any bottle over $40 to protect your investment and ensure optimal flavor development.</p>

