  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon and Bordeaux?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon typically shows riper, more concentrated fruit flavors with higher alcohol (14-15%) due to California's warmer climate, while Bordeaux exhibits more earthy, mineral-driven characteristics with moderate alcohol levels. Napa wines often feature bold blackcurrant and vanilla oak notes, whereas Bordeaux emphasizes elegance and complexity through blending with Merlot and other varietals. Both represent world-class expressions of Cabernet Sauvignon, but Napa's style tends to be more immediately approachable and fruit-forward.</p>
