    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What are the best alternatives to expensive Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Explore exceptional value in Washington State's Columbia Valley (Quilceda Creek, Woodward Canyon) or Paso Robles producers like Tablas Creek and L'Aventure, which offer similar power and concentration. Within California, consider Sonoma County's Alexander Valley or Knights Valley appellations, which produce Cabernet Sauvignon with Napa-like richness at lower prices. These regions share similar climate patterns and winemaking philosophies while offering distinctive terroir expressions at more accessible price points.</p>
